# 5. Understanding Fields

AWK divides each input line into fields.

Example:

```text
101 Ravi Support Hyderabad 45000
```

AWK sees:

```text
$1 = 101

$2 = Ravi

$3 = Support

$4 = Hyderabad

$5 = 45000
```

The complete line is:

```text
$0
```

This is one of the most important AWK concepts.

