# 44. Count Matching Records

Count Support employees:

```bash
awk '$3=="Support" {count++} END {print count}' employees.txt
```

Better labeled output:

```bash
awk '$3=="Support" {count++} END {print "Support Employees:", count+0}' employees.txt
```

Why `count+0`?

If there are no matches, an uninitialized AWK variable may print as an empty string in some contexts.

Adding zero forces numeric output.

