# 45. Calculate Total Salary

```bash
awk '{sum += $5} END {print "Total Salary:", sum}' employees.txt
```

How it works:

```text
Line 1 salary
    ↓
Add to sum

Line 2 salary
    ↓
Add to sum

Continue...

END
    ↓
Print total
```

---

# 46. Calculate Average

```bash
awk '{sum += $5} END {print "Average Salary:", sum/NR}' employees.txt
```

Safer version:

```bash
awk '
{
    sum += $5
}
END {
    if (NR > 0)
        print "Average Salary:", sum/NR
    else
        print "No records"
}
' employees.txt
```

This avoids division by zero for empty input.

