# 47. Find Maximum Value

```bash
awk '
NR==1 {
    max=$5
    name=$2
}
$5>max {
    max=$5
    name=$2
}
END {
    print name, max
}
' employees.txt
```

This prints the employee with the highest salary.

Why initialize with the first record?

Because assuming:

```text
max=0
```

can be wrong when data can contain negative values.

