# 77. AWK with Logs

Suppose:

```text
2026-07-08 10:00:01 INFO PaymentService started
2026-07-08 10:01:10 ERROR PaymentService timeout
2026-07-08 10:02:20 WARN DatabaseService slow
```

If whitespace is the separator:

```bash
awk '{print $1, $2, $3, $4}' application.log
```

But real logs can contain variable message text, JSON, tabs, or custom delimiters.

Understand the log format before assuming field numbers.

