# 83. PSA Scenario – Disk Usage Investigation

Check:

```bash
df -P
```

Then:

```bash
df -P | awk '
NR>1 {
    usage=$5
    gsub(/%/, "", usage)

    if (usage >= 80)
        print $6, usage "%"
}
'
```

This identifies mount points meeting the threshold.

But do not jump directly to:

```bash
rm -rf ...
```

A correct PSA workflow is:

```text
Identify high-usage filesystem
        ↓
Identify large directories
        ↓
Identify large files
        ↓
Check whether files are active
        ↓
Check retention and ownership
        ↓
Follow approved cleanup procedure
        ↓
Verify disk recovery
        ↓
Validate application health
```

